    "body": "```\n.cpu_local: alloc10112 0\ncpu_local_alloc_set: alloc10112\ncpu_local_start=0xffffffff80ff0000\nself=0x400010\nerror: abnormal termination: the program aborted execution\n  --> /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:91:5\n   |\n91 |     abort();\n   |     ^^^^^^^ abnormal termination occurred here\n   |\n   = note: stack backtrace:\n           0: osdk_test_kernel::panic_handler\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:91:5: 91:12\n           1: osdk_test_kernel::__ostd_panic_handler\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:88:1: 88:30\n           2: panic\n               at src/main.rs:30:14: 30:40\n           3: ostd::cpu::local::CpuLocalCell::<u32>::store\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/cpu/local/cell.rs:250:22: 250:67\n           4: ostd::cpu::id::current::init_on_cpu\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/cpu/id.rs:169:9: 169:42\n           5: ostd::cpu::id::init_on_bsp\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/cpu/id.rs:197:14: 197:37\n           6: ostd::cpu::init_on_bsp\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/cpu/mod.rs:42:14: 42:39\n           7: ostd::init\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/lib.rs:132:14: 132:32\n           8: ostd::boot::start_kernel\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs:138:14: 138:27\n           9: ostd::arch::boot::miri_boot\n               at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/arch/miri/boot/mod.rs:73:14: 73:28\n           10: miri_start\n               at src/main.rs:20:5: 20:34\n```\n\n```rust\n// ostd::cpu::local::CpuLocalCell::<u32>::store\nimpl<T: 'static + SingleInstructionStore> CpuLocalCell<T> {\n    /// Writes a value to the per-CPU object in a single instruction.\n    ///\n    /// Note that this memory operation will not be elided or reordered by the\n    /// compiler since it is a black-box.\n    pub fn store(&'static self, val: T) {\n        miri_println!(\"cpu_local_start=0x{:x}\\nself={:p}\", cpu_local_start(), self);\n        let offset = self as *const _ as usize - cpu_local_start();\n        // SAFETY: The CPU-local object is defined in the `.cpu_local` section,\n        // so the pointer to the object is valid. And the reference is never shared.\n        unsafe {\n            T::store(offset, val);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is because `&self` refers to a paddr, while cpu_local_start is a vaddr, then substraction overflows.\n\n```\nfn cpu_local_start() -> usize {\n    #[cfg(miri)]\n    return 0xffff_ffff_8000_0000usize + 4080 * PAGE_SIZE;\n    #[cfg(not(miri))]\n    return addr::__cpu_local_start as *const () as usize;\n}\n```",
